-- allium: 3
-- specs/dflash/dflash_server_cli.allium
--
-- Scope: the implementation contract for the llama-server CLI path
-- that turns `--spec-type dflash -md <drafter.gguf> --parallel N`
-- into a working multi-slot DFlash deployment. The abstract DFlash
-- pipeline (combine_features, inject_kv_fused × L_d, drafter_forward,
-- drafter_lm_head, sample-and-accept) is owned by specs/dflash/dflash.allium.
-- THIS spec narrows the SERVER-SIDE wiring: how the sidecar is loaded,
-- how the per-slot bindings are constructed, how the orchestrator's
-- batched fan-out is reached from process_batch_tokens, and how the
-- sample/accept loop addresses per-stream logits without faulting at
-- np >= 2.
--
-- Status: every contract below is HONOURED ON HEAD as of 2026-05-21
-- (post-P0.A.4 closure, submodule commit cad6b591). The spec exists as
-- a regression guard against future server-CLI refactors silently
-- breaking the multi-slot DFlash path — not as a backlog of pending
-- work.
--
-- Why this spec exists: P0.A had four sub-issues to close before Tier 2
-- prerequisite work could land. P0.A.4 specifically was a SEGV in
-- llama_sampling_prepare at --parallel 2: the per-stream dispatch
-- introduced by PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_4D N2.d (Bug C structural fix) split
-- the combined `batch` into one llama_decode per slot per tick. The
-- engine resets output_ids on every llama_decode and indexes it in the
-- LOCAL frame [0..n_tokens) of the dispatched batch_view. The
-- pre-existing speculative_decoding_accept() walked all slots and
-- read their verify logits via slot.i_batch_dft[k] — a GLOBAL-frame
-- index recorded at common_batch_add time. At np=2 with --draft-max 4,
-- slot 1's i_batch_dft[0]=5 falls outside slot 0's just-decoded
-- output_ids window; llama_get_logits_ith hit
-- `batch.logits[5] != true` and the server SIGSEGV'd. The fix:
-- scope speculative_decoding_accept to a single run_seq_id and
-- translate i_batch_dft from global to local frame before any
-- llama_get_logits_ith / get_embeddings_ith call. THIS spec binds
-- that fix so the index frame and the per-stream scoping cannot drift
-- silently in future server-CLI work.
--
-- Includes:
--   - External entities for the runtime objects the wiring touches
--     (the target llama_context, the sidecar drafter, the per-slot
--     common_speculative wrapper, the combined batch and its
--     per-run batch_view, the per-slot i_batch_dft index list).
--   - Contracts for the five load-bearing properties:
--       SidecarSharesTargetTokenizer
--       OrchestratorInvokedFromServerCLI
--       PerSlotSeqIdBinding
--       BatchedFanOutContract
--       MultiSlotSamplingContract
--   - A derived system-wide invariant MultiSlotSEGVAbsence that
--     composes the per-stream split with MultiSlotSamplingContract
--     to bind absence of the regressed
--     `batch.logits[N] != true` runtime failure.
--   - Cross-references to specs/dflash/dflash.allium (abstract DFlash
--     contracts) and specs/dflash/cb_eval_residual_capture.allium
--     (the residual-capture surface the orchestrator depends on).
--
-- Excludes:
--   - The drafter's internal kernel pipeline. Owned by
--     specs/dflash/dflash.allium contracts ProjectAndFuse and
--     DraftBlockEmit.
--   - The cb_eval residual extract surface (mechanism + scheduler
--     fast-path constraints). Owned by
--     specs/dflash/cb_eval_residual_capture.allium.
--   - Per-stream KV layout invariants. Owned by
--     specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium.
--   - The single-slot DFlash CLI driver
--     (examples/dflash-speculative-simple/dflash-speculative-simple.cpp).
--     That binary does not exercise the server's per-stream split;
--     it has its own decode loop.

-- ============================================================
-- External entities — runtime objects we constrain
-- ============================================================

-- The target llama_context the server boots. Carries vocab/embedding
-- (token_embd.weight / output.weight) which the DFlash sidecar
-- REUSES rather than carrying its own. Lives in src/llama-context.h
-- and is constructed by llama_init_from_gpt_params via
-- examples/server/server-context.cpp:121-124.
external entity TargetContext {
    vocab_size: Integer
    lm_head_dtype: TensorDtype
    n_seq_max: Integer              -- mirrors cparams.n_seq_max; production = 2
    has_dflash_binding: Boolean     -- true after llama_set_dflash succeeds
}

-- The DFlash sidecar drafter, loaded from the path supplied via
-- `-md <path>` and routed to llama_dflash_drafter_load via
-- params_base.speculative.mparams_dft.path. The sidecar is NOT a
-- standalone llama_model: it has no tokenizer and no embedding;
-- token_embd / output are borrowed from the target. Lives at
-- src/llama-dflash.cpp:225-310 (llama_dflash_drafter_load).
external entity DflashSidecar {
    path: String
    n_layers: Integer
    block_size: Integer             -- BS; constrains draft length per cycle
    sliding_window: Integer         -- SWA bound; constrains drafter K/V depth
    target_layer_ids: List<Integer> -- source layers for residual extract
    -- The sidecar carries NO vocab of its own. The drafter operates
    -- in the target's embedding/logit space; the drafter_lm_head
    -- kernel multiplies drafter hiddens against ctx.target_lm_head
    -- (src/llama-dflash.cpp:836-838).
    has_own_vocab: Boolean          -- always false; structurally enforced
}

-- The per-slot common_speculative wrapper. One per server slot
-- (server-context.cpp:333), each binds a DFlash impl to ctx_tgt
-- with the slot's seq_id. Owns a common_speculative_state_dflash
-- (common/speculative.cpp:969-1096) that holds the drafter pointer
-- and the seq_id. The drafter pointer is SHARED across slots via
-- the share-the-bind path at common/speculative.cpp:992-999
-- (llama_get_dflash_drafter returns the existing binding so the
-- second and subsequent slots reuse it rather than reloading the
-- GGUF).
external entity SlotSpec {
    slot_id: Integer                -- 0..n_seq_max-1
    seq_id: Integer                 -- = slot_id; passed at init
    impl_type: SpecImplType         -- = dflash for this spec
    owns_drafter: Boolean           -- only slot 0 typically owns
}

-- A per-stream slice of the combined batch dispatched by
-- process_batch_tokens. The combined batch is assembled by
-- add_sampled_tokens + batch_pending_prompt in update_slots
-- (server-context.cpp:4982, 4985, 4997) and indexed in the GLOBAL
-- frame [0..batch.n_tokens). Each slot's i_batch_dft[k] is a
-- GLOBAL-frame index recorded by common_batch_add at append time
-- (server-context.cpp:3305, 3322, etc.). Construction of the view
-- is at server-context.cpp:4647-4674: the loop walks the combined
-- batch from i=0, identifies the contiguous run with the same
-- primary seq_id (run_seq_id), and builds a batch_view starting at
-- offset `i` with `n_tokens` rows. The view's index frame is
-- LOCAL [0..n_tokens). Each such view is handed to llama_decode,
-- which resets output_ids and addresses logits in the view's local
-- frame.
external entity BatchView {
    batch_offset: Integer           -- start index in the combined batch
    n_tokens: Integer
    run_seq_id: Integer             -- uniform across all rows
}

-- The per-slot deferred logits index list. Pushed in the GLOBAL
-- frame by common_batch_add at each verify-batch row append (see
-- server-context.cpp:3305 etc.). Consumed by speculative_decoding_accept
-- after the per-stream llama_decode of that slot's BatchView
-- returns. Stored on server_slot.i_batch_dft.
external entity SlotVerifyIndexList {
    slot_id: Integer
    global_indices: List<Integer>   -- recorded global-frame indices
}

-- ============================================================
-- Enumerations
-- ============================================================

-- The dtype the target's lm_head must carry for DFlash to bind.
-- llama_set_dflash explicitly rejects non-F16 lm_head at
-- src/llama-dflash.cpp:444-452: "target token_embd / output.weight
-- must both be F16". The lm_head-f16 recast target variant
-- (V-F1.T1.lm_head-f16.gguf) is the production input.
enum TensorDtype { f32 | f16 | bf16 | q4_0 | other }

-- The speculative implementation a SlotSpec wraps. Mirrors
-- enum common_speculative_type in common/speculative.h.
enum SpecImplType {
    none | draft | mtp | eagle3
  | ngram_simple | ngram_map_k | ngram_map_k4v | ngram_mod | ngram_cache
  | suffix | dflash
}

-- ============================================================
-- Config
-- ============================================================

config {
    -- The maximum --parallel value the multi-slot wiring must
    -- support. Mirrors cparams.n_seq_max at llama_set_dflash time
    -- (src/llama-dflash.cpp:487). Production runs with 2;
    -- alloc_ctx_scratch is sized for the full n_slots_cap regardless
    -- of how many slots are active.
    max_parallel_slots: Integer = 8

    -- The default draft block length: --draft-max. Production
    -- profile sets this to 4 (qwen36-27b-x2-dflash.sh:35).
    -- The drafter's internal BS is fixed at 4 in
    -- src/llama-dflash.cpp:690.
    default_draft_max: Integer = 4
}

-- ============================================================
-- Contracts
-- ============================================================

-- Contract 1: The DFlash sidecar drafter does NOT carry its own
-- tokenizer or vocabulary; it operates in the TARGET's embedding /
-- logit space. Token IDs the drafter emits are valid target token
-- IDs by construction because the drafter_lm_head kernel projects
-- drafter hiddens against the target's output.weight tensor.
--
-- Tied to source:
--   - sidecar GGUF schema:
--       src/llama-dflash.cpp:225-310 (llama_dflash_drafter_load)
--       reads only `dflash.*` keys — no tokenizer.ggml.tokens, no
--       tokenizer.ggml.model. The "drafter loaded:" log at line 306
--       explicitly prints "vocab(target)=?" to flag that vocab
--       belongs to the target.
--   - shared tensors:
--       src/llama-dflash.cpp:441-468 — llama_set_dflash resolves
--       token_embd.weight + output.weight FROM THE TARGET and stores
--       pointers in ctx_tgt->dflash_state. target_vocab_size is read
--       from target's token_embd.weight->ne[1] (line 467), never
--       from the sidecar.
--   - drafter lm_head dispatch:
--       src/llama-dflash.cpp:836-838 — drafter_lm_head_launch
--       multiplies st.d_drafter_hidden against st.target_lm_head;
--       output rows have V = ctx.target_vocab_size columns.
--   - server wiring:
--       examples/server/server-context.cpp:150-156, 188-196 — the
--       `is_dflash_spec` branch routes the `-md` path into
--       mparams_dft.path and SKIPS the standalone draft-model load
--       (no llama_model_load_from_file for the sidecar; the sidecar
--       is not a standalone llama_model).
contract SidecarSharesTargetTokenizer {
    invoke: (target: TargetContext, sidecar: DflashSidecar) -> TargetContext

    @invariant DrafterCarriesNoVocab
        -- The sidecar GGUF contains only `dflash.*` keys and per-layer
        -- weight tensors. No tokenizer.ggml.* keys, no token_embd
        -- tensor, no output tensor of its own. sidecar.has_own_vocab
        -- is false by construction.

    @invariant TargetSuppliesEmbedAndLMHead
        -- After llama_set_dflash succeeds, ctx_tgt->dflash_state
        -- holds two device pointers borrowed from the target:
        -- target_token_embd and target_lm_head, each addressing
        -- the target's [vocab_size, D_emb] tensor. The kernel
        -- pipeline reads these pointers; there is no second
        -- embedding table in flight.

    @invariant TargetLMHeadMustBeF16
        -- llama_set_dflash rejects (returns LLAMA_DFLASH_INVALID_DRAFTER)
        -- unless target_token_embd and target_lm_head are both F16.
        -- BF16 lm_head requires the lm_head-f16 recast variant of the
        -- target GGUF (the production profile uses
        -- V-F1.T1.lm_head-f16.gguf). target.lm_head_dtype = f16 is
        -- the prerequisite for has_dflash_binding becoming true.

    @invariant TokenSpaceEquivalence
        -- Every llama_token the drafter emits is a valid token in the
        -- TARGET vocabulary, because the per-row argmax at
        -- src/llama-dflash.cpp:847-850 ranges over [0, V) where
        -- V = target.vocab_size. The drafter cannot emit out-of-vocab
        -- IDs for the target verifier.
}

-- Contract 2: When the server is started with `--spec-type dflash`
-- and a non-empty `-md <path>`, every active slot receives a
-- common_speculative initialised with a DFlash impl. The orchestrator
-- multi-slot fan-out (common_speculative_draft_batched) is the
-- entry point at np >= 2; the per-slot fallback path
-- (common_speculative_draft) is the np = 1 path. Both paths
-- ultimately dispatch into llama_dflash_draft_batch.
--
-- Tied to source:
--   - CLI flag parsing:
--       common/common.cpp:1082 — `-md` / `--model-draft` populates
--       params.speculative.model.
--       common/common.cpp:1087 — `--spec-type` parses the enum
--       (none | ngram-cache | ngram-simple | ngram-map-k | ngram-map-k4v
--       | ngram-mod | suffix | mtp | dflash).
--   - server load-model branch:
--       examples/server/server-context.cpp:156 — is_dflash_spec gate
--       on params_base.speculative.type == COMMON_SPECULATIVE_TYPE_DFLASH.
--       Lines 188-196 route the GGUF path to mparams_dft.path.
--   - per-slot init:
--       examples/server/server-context.cpp:333 — every slot in
--       [0, n_parallel) calls
--       common_speculative_init(params_base.speculative, ctx, slot.id).
--   - DFlash impl construction:
--       common/speculative.cpp:1224-1234 — has_dflash gate.
--       common/speculative.cpp:1320-1332 — case COMMON_SPECULATIVE_TYPE_DFLASH
--       constructs common_speculative_state_dflash; first slot loads
--       the GGUF and binds via llama_set_dflash; subsequent slots
--       reuse via llama_get_dflash_drafter (common/speculative.cpp:992-999).
--   - orchestrator entry (multi-slot):
--       common/speculative.cpp:1481-1641 — common_speculative_draft_batched
--       checks all_dflash + shared ctx_tgt at lines 1554-1559, then
--       performs a single llama_dflash_draft_batch call for all
--       slots (line 1592-1596). Falls back to per-slot serial if
--       the shape is mixed or N <= 1.
--   - orchestrator entry (single-slot):
--       common/speculative.cpp:1429-1471 — common_speculative_draft
--       loops over spec->impls and calls impl->draft(); the DFlash
--       impl's draft() dispatches through
--       llama_dflash_draft_batch(n_slots=1, ...) at
--       common/speculative.cpp:1071-1074 — preserving regression
--       coverage between np=1 and np>=2 (the trampoline at
--       src/llama-dflash.cpp:634-649 enforces byte-identical behaviour).
contract OrchestratorInvokedFromServerCLI {
    invoke: (target: TargetContext, sidecar: DflashSidecar, n_slots: Integer) -> TargetContext

    @invariant SidecarPathRoutedThroughCLI
        -- When params_base.speculative.type =
        -- COMMON_SPECULATIVE_TYPE_DFLASH and
        -- params_base.speculative.model is non-empty, the path is
        -- assigned to params_base.speculative.mparams_dft.path and
        -- the standalone draft-model loader at
        -- server-context.cpp:197-240 is bypassed.

    @invariant EveryActiveSlotInitsDFlash
        -- For every slot in [0, params_base.n_parallel), the loop
        -- at server-context.cpp:253-353 calls common_speculative_init
        -- with the slot's seq_id. When type = DFLASH, this produces a
        -- common_speculative_state_dflash whose drafter pointer is
        -- either the first-slot-loaded drafter (owns_drafter=true)
        -- or a shared reference via llama_get_dflash_drafter
        -- (owns_drafter=false).

    @invariant MultiSlotEntryIsBatched
        -- At n_slots >= 2 with all-DFlash + shared ctx_tgt, the
        -- caller (e.g. update_slots → common_speculative_draft_batched)
        -- dispatches through llama_dflash_draft_batch in a single
        -- call. The per-slot serial fallback is reachable only when
        -- one or more slots are non-DFlash or carry a different
        -- ctx_tgt (common/speculative.cpp:1541-1559).

    @invariant SingleSlotIsBatchedTrampoline
        -- At n_slots = 1, common_speculative_draft calls
        -- common_speculative_state_dflash::draft, which dispatches
        -- into llama_dflash_draft_batch with n_slots=1. The
        -- single-slot trampoline at src/llama-dflash.cpp:634-649 is
        -- byte-identical to the legacy llama_dflash_draft. There is
        -- no separate np=1 kernel path that np>=2 could diverge from.
}

-- Contract 3: Each slot's common_speculative_state_dflash wraps the
-- same shared llama_context (ctx_tgt) but is tagged with a unique
-- seq_id ∈ [0, n_slots). The drafter pointer is shared across
-- slots; the per-slot CONTEXT MAPPING is the seq_id, not a separate
-- llama_context copy. This is the post-D9.5 collapsed-context
-- invariant that common_speculative_draft_batched assumes at lines
-- 1522-1532 (MTP) and lines 1554-1559 (DFlash).
--
-- Tied to source:
--   - per-slot seq_id binding:
--       common/speculative.cpp:1324-1325 — common_speculative_state_dflash
--       is constructed with seq_id passed through from
--       common_speculative_init's `llama_seq_id seq_id` parameter.
--   - shared ctx, shared drafter:
--       common/speculative.cpp:983-987 — the constructor captures
--       ctx_tgt_ + seq_id_ into the state.
--       common/speculative.cpp:992-999 — share-the-bind path:
--       llama_get_dflash_drafter returns the existing binding so
--       the second slot reuses it (owns_drafter=false).
--   - server slot.id → seq_id propagation:
--       examples/server/server-context.cpp:256, 333 — slot.id = i in
--       [0, n_parallel); common_speculative_init is called with
--       slot.id as the seq_id argument. Therefore SlotSpec.seq_id =
--       SlotSpec.slot_id by construction at server level.
--   - cross-slot ctx invariance:
--       common/speculative.cpp:1554-1559 — the batched path asserts
--       df_states[i]->ctx_tgt = df_states[0]->ctx_tgt for every i.
--       The fan-out is rejected (all_dflash = false → serial
--       fallback) if any slot wraps a different ctx_tgt.
contract PerSlotSeqIdBinding {
    invoke: (target: TargetContext, slots: List<SlotSpec>) -> List<SlotSpec>

    @invariant AllSlotsShareCtxTarget
        -- For every pair of SlotSpecs in the same server instance,
        -- their underlying common_speculative_state_dflash captures
        -- the same ctx_tgt pointer. There is exactly one
        -- llama_context per server; per-slot speculative state is a
        -- wrapper, not a context copy.

    @invariant SeqIdMatchesSlotId
        -- For every SlotSpec, seq_id = slot_id. The server passes
        -- slot.id straight through to common_speculative_init's
        -- seq_id parameter; the DFlash state stores it for use as
        -- the seq_id field on llama_dflash_draft_batch's seq_ids[]
        -- argument (common/speculative.cpp:1589).

    @invariant SeqIdsAreUniqueAcrossSlots
        -- Within a single server instance, slots have distinct ids
        -- (server-context.cpp:256 assigns slot.id = i in the slot
        -- creation loop). Therefore distinct slots dispatch with
        -- distinct seq_ids, and the kernel's per-slot K/V cache
        -- offsets (src/llama-dflash.cpp:768-769) are non-overlapping.

    @invariant DrafterPointerIsShared
        -- Exactly one of the slots holds owns_drafter=true (the slot
        -- whose init triggered llama_dflash_drafter_load); the
        -- remainder hold owns_drafter=false and share the same
        -- drafter pointer via llama_get_dflash_drafter. The
        -- destructor at common/speculative.cpp:1020-1026 frees the
        -- drafter exactly once, gated on owns_drafter. The GGUF is
        -- loaded once per server, not once per slot.
}

-- Contract 4: llama_dflash_draft_batch is the kernel-level API the
-- orchestrator dispatches into. Its signature and per-slot stride
-- semantics are load-bearing on the multi-slot fan-out.
--
-- Tied to source:
--   - declaration:
--       include/llama.h:1848 — LLAMA_API int32_t
--       llama_dflash_draft_batch(ctx, n_slots, anchor_token_ids,
--       anchor_positions, seq_ids, out_candidates, max_total_candidates).
--   - definition:
--       src/llama-dflash.cpp:671-871 — implementation.
--   - per-slot stride + capacity check:
--       src/llama-dflash.cpp:690-695 — BS = 4; max_total_candidates
--       must be at least BS * n_slots.
--   - per-slot pipeline dispatch:
--       src/llama-dflash.cpp:734-773 — stage_target_hiddens +
--       combine_features + inject_kv_fused × L_d run with N_slots=1
--       per slot at the slot's pointer offset.
--   - shape-uniform multi-slot fan-out:
--       src/llama-dflash.cpp:822-833 — drafter_forward_launch is
--       called once with N_slots=n_slots; the kernel's storage
--       stride uses n_slots_cap (bind-time capacity), not the
--       dispatch count. This is the feedback_drafter_forward_n_slots_cap
--       lesson from Phase 4 multi-slot landing.
--   - per-slot argmax write-back:
--       src/llama-dflash.cpp:847-850 — out_candidates is written
--       slot-major: slot s occupies BS contiguous rows starting at
--       index s * BS. The caller's per_slot = rc / N decode at
--       common/speculative.cpp:1599 reverses this layout.
--   - n_max_block ceiling at orchestrator level:
--       common/speculative.cpp:1600 — n_max_block = min(params.n_max,
--       per_slot). The caller truncates the per-slot draft list to
--       the requested n_max even if the kernel wrote BS rows.
contract BatchedFanOutContract {
    invoke: (target: TargetContext, sidecar: DflashSidecar, n_slots: Integer) -> Integer

    @invariant CapacityIsNSlotsTimesBlockSize
        -- max_total_candidates >= n_slots * BS, where BS =
        -- sidecar.block_size (=4 in src/llama-dflash.cpp:690 for the
        -- production Qwen3.6-27B DFlash drafter). Smaller capacity
        -- returns LLAMA_DFLASH_INVALID_DRAFTER (line 691-695).

    @invariant SlotMajorOutputStride
        -- out_candidates is laid out [n_slots, per_slot] with per_slot
        -- = rc / n_slots. Slot s's draft list occupies indices
        -- [s * per_slot, (s + 1) * per_slot). The caller MUST decode
        -- with this stride or slots will be confused with each
        -- other's drafts.

    @invariant SeqIdsPassedThroughToKernel
        -- The seq_ids[N] argument is passed through to the
        -- per-layer inject_kv_fused dispatch as the slot indexing
        -- key into the [L_d, n_slots_cap, SeqLen, ...] K/V cache
        -- (src/llama-dflash.cpp:768). Distinct seq_ids therefore
        -- write/read non-overlapping slot regions, preserving
        -- cross-slot isolation.

    @invariant NSlotsCapIsKernelStorageStride
        -- The kernel addresses per-layer K/V via
        -- l * n_slots_cap * SeqLen * H_kv * D_h + s * SeqLen * H_kv * D_h.
        -- n_slots_cap is the BIND-TIME capacity (captured at
        -- llama_set_dflash from ctx_tgt->cparams.n_seq_max,
        -- src/llama-dflash.cpp:487); n_slots is the per-dispatch
        -- count. They are decoupled; the kernel must not collapse
        -- them.

    @invariant NMaxBlockBoundsPerSlot
        -- The orchestrator's effective per-slot draft length is
        -- min(params.n_max, per_slot). Even when the kernel produces
        -- BS candidates per slot, the caller truncates to n_max
        -- (default 4 in production; matches BS exactly for this
        -- drafter, so no truncation is observed in the production
        -- profile).
}

-- Contract 5: At n_slots >= 2, the server's per-stream split in
-- process_batch_tokens dispatches ONE llama_decode per slot per
-- tick (Bug C structural fix from PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_4D N2.d). Inside
-- the loop, speculative_decoding_accept(batch_offset, run_seq_id)
-- is called once per dispatched batch_view. It processes only the
-- slot whose slot.id = run_seq_id and translates i_batch_dft from
-- the GLOBAL combined-batch frame to the LOCAL batch_view frame
-- by subtracting batch_offset, before any llama_get_logits_ith or
-- llama_decoder_get_embeddings_ith call.
--
-- This is the P0.A.4 closure invariant. It is load-bearing: the
-- prior implementation walked all slots per call and faulted with
-- `batch.logits[N] != true` at np>=2.
--
-- Tied to source:
--   - per-stream loop:
--       examples/server/server-context.cpp:4647-4674 — the loop
--       walks batch from i=0, identifies the contiguous primary
--       seq_id run (run_seq_id), constructs batch_view starting at
--       offset i with run length capped by n_batch.
--   - in-loop call site:
--       examples/server/server-context.cpp:4945-4947 — after the
--       per-stream llama_decode, calls
--       speculative_decoding_accept(i, run_seq_id). i is the run's
--       start in the combined batch frame; run_seq_id is the
--       single slot whose tokens were just submitted.
--   - signature change:
--       examples/server/server-context.h:412 —
--       void speculative_decoding_accept(int32_t batch_offset, int run_seq_id);
--   - Phase A run scoping:
--       examples/server/server-context.cpp:4194-4206 — slot iteration
--       skips slots where slot.id != run_seq_id with a comment
--       documenting why: "Another slot's verify tokens belong to a
--       different run; its decode either hasn't happened yet
--       (output_ids will be -1 in this run's frame) or already
--       happened earlier (its output_ids has since been overwritten
--       by THIS run's decode)."
--   - i_batch_dft global → local translation:
--       examples/server/server-context.cpp:4214-4221 — builds
--       idx_local from slot.i_batch_dft by subtracting
--       batch_offset. Subsequent llama_get_logits_ith /
--       llama_decoder_get_embeddings_ith calls (lines 4224, 4234,
--       4240) consume idx_local.
--   - i_batch_dft is recorded in the GLOBAL frame:
--       examples/server/server-context.cpp:3305, 3322, 3391, 3403,
--       3459, 3471 — every common_batch_add accompanying push_back
--       records batch.n_tokens at the moment of append, which is
--       the global combined-batch frame index.
contract MultiSlotSamplingContract {
    invoke: (view: BatchView, slot: SlotSpec, idx: SlotVerifyIndexList) -> SlotVerifyIndexList

    @invariant CalledOncePerStreamDispatch
        -- For every BatchView dispatched by process_batch_tokens,
        -- speculative_decoding_accept is invoked exactly once at
        -- server-context.cpp:4947, receiving the view's
        -- (batch_offset, run_seq_id).

    @invariant OnlyRunSeqIdSlotIsRead
        -- Inside speculative_decoding_accept Phase A, slots are
        -- skipped unless slot.id = run_seq_id. No
        -- llama_get_logits_ith or llama_decoder_get_embeddings_ith
        -- call is issued for any other slot in this invocation.
        -- The skipped slots' verify reads happen in their own
        -- per-stream invocation later in the loop.

    @invariant GlobalToLocalFrameTranslation
        -- For the run_seq_id slot, every entry g in
        -- slot.i_batch_dft is translated to local frame as
        -- (g - batch_offset) before being passed to
        -- llama_get_logits_ith. The translated index lies in
        -- [0, view.n_tokens) by construction (the per-stream split
        -- guarantees the slot's verify rows are contiguous within
        -- the current view).

    @invariant TwoPhaseSplitPreserved
        -- Phase A (the read-only block at server-context.cpp:4193-4249)
        -- collects logits/embeddings + accepted-token IDs into
        -- per-slot `accepted_slot` records BEFORE any state mutation.
        -- Phase B (lines 4252-) applies the mutation
        -- (restore_speculative_checkpoint, mtp_accept_tokens, etc.)
        -- which may internally re-issue llama_decode and clobber
        -- output_ids. Phase A's reads must finish before Phase B
        -- begins; the in-function ordering enforces this.
}

-- ============================================================
-- Invariants — system-wide
-- ============================================================

-- The composition invariant. The per-stream split in
-- process_batch_tokens (PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_4D N2.d) plus the
-- per-stream-scoped speculative_decoding_accept (this spec's
-- MultiSlotSamplingContract) together guarantee that
-- llama_get_logits_ith never reads a logit index that was not
-- enabled by the most recent llama_decode. The runtime fault
-- `batch.logits[N] != true` does not arise.
--
-- Property-test generation off this invariant should produce a
-- regression test that boots the server at --parallel >= 2 with
-- --spec-type dflash + a non-empty -md path, sends concurrent
-- /v1/completions requests, and asserts no `batch.logits[*] != true`
-- log line surfaces. The existing
-- scripts/test-server-multi-slot-dflash.sh script (parent commit
-- a12609a) is the binding test referenced by the P0.A.4 closure.
invariant MultiSlotSEGVAbsence {
    for slot in SlotSpecs:
        for view in BatchViews:
            (slot.slot_id = view.run_seq_id)
            implies
            (view.n_tokens > 0)
}

-- The structural property that gives the above invariant teeth.
-- Every entry in a slot's i_batch_dft for the currently-dispatched
-- view, after global-to-local translation, lies in the engine's
-- enabled output_ids window for that view.
invariant TranslatedIndicesAreInWindow {
    for view in BatchViews:
        for slot in SlotSpecs:
            for g in slot_global_indices(slot, view):
                (slot.slot_id = view.run_seq_id)
                implies
                (g - view.batch_offset >= 0
                 and g - view.batch_offset < view.n_tokens)
}

-- Helper black box function: returns the GLOBAL-frame index list
-- recorded for `slot` that belongs to the current dispatch's run.
-- Concrete implementation reads SlotVerifyIndexList.global_indices
-- and filters to indices in [view.batch_offset,
-- view.batch_offset + view.n_tokens).
-- slot_global_indices(slot, view) — see comment above.

-- ============================================================
-- Open questions
-- ============================================================

-- OQ-PARALLEL-CAP-SOURCE
-- max_parallel_slots above is the spec's upper bound on the wiring
-- (config default 8). The runtime cap on a given binding is
-- ctx_tgt->cparams.n_seq_max, captured by llama_set_dflash into
-- n_slots_cap (src/llama-dflash.cpp:487) and used as the kernel's
-- per-layer K/V stride. Production runs with n_seq_max=2 today;
-- larger values would require revisiting alloc_ctx_scratch's
-- VRAM budget. This spec binds the WIRING property
-- (every active slot is initialised, every active slot dispatches
-- through the orchestrator); the VRAM ceiling is a separate
-- concern owned by the production profile.

-- OQ-DRAFTER-VOCAB-DRIFT-DETECTION
-- The current implementation does NOT compare a sidecar-side
-- vocab record against the target's vocab — the sidecar simply
-- has no vocab. If a future drafter format gains tokenizer
-- metadata (e.g. for cross-tokenizer DFlash variants), the
-- SidecarSharesTargetTokenizer contract becomes a runtime check
-- rather than a structural fact. Decide before that variant ships
-- whether the check belongs in llama_dflash_drafter_load or in
-- llama_set_dflash (the latter has access to ctx_tgt and can
-- compare against target vocab_size directly).

-- @guidance
--     This spec intentionally binds the SERVER-CLI surface only.
--     The single-slot dflash-speculative-simple CLI driver has its
--     own decode loop (no per-stream split, no
--     speculative_decoding_accept) and is governed by
--     specs/dflash/dflash.allium plus the per-cycle math therein.
--     Server-side regressions surface against this spec via the
--     scripts/test-server-multi-slot-dflash.sh harness; the
--     libllama-level DFlash tests in tests/dflash-speculative/
--     (test-dflash-np-multislot, test-dflash-closure) cover the
--     contracts the orchestrator depends on at the C API layer
--     and run unmodified after server-CLI refactors.
